AMEND S e n ate Bill No. 2414* House Bill No. 2278
by deleting all language after the enacting clause and substituting:
SECTION 1. Tennessee Code Annotated, Section 68-11-1303, is amended by adding
the following as new subsections:
(i)
(1) Any certificate of public advantage in effect on June 30, 2028, automatically
expires; provided, that any pricing restrictions in a certificate of public advantage that are
in effect as of the expiration date remain in effect until the earlier of the fifth anniversary
of the expiration date or the date that a new inpatient acute care hospital opens in the
geographic service area covered by the expired certificate of public advantage.
(2) After June 30, 2028, the pricing restrictions must be supervised by the
attorney general and reporter pursuant to a supervision agreement, and may only be
modified by the mutual written agreement of the entity subject to the pricing restrictions
and the attorney general and reporter. The entity subject to the pricing restrictions is
responsible for the costs of the attorney general and reporter's supervision of the pricing
restrictions.
(3) This section does not limit or impair the authority of the attorney general and
reporter to enforce state or federal antitrust law.
(j) Notwithstanding part 16 of this chapter, or another law to the contrary, an acute care
hospital in the same geographical area that a certificate of public advantage expired pursuant to
subsection (i) is not required to obtain a certificate of need pursuant to § 68-11-1607.
